William I. BETTIS v. PATTERSON-BALLAGH CORPORATION, etc. No. 8905. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. July 29, 1938. Raymond Ibes Blakeslee, of Los An-geles, Cal., for appellant. Lyon & Lyon, of Los Angeles, Cal., for appellee.

Before GARRECHT, DENMAN, and MATHEWS, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Upon stipulation of counsel for respective parties, ordered appeal herein dismissed, that a decree of dismissal be filed and entered accordingly, and that the mandate of the court in this cause issue forthwith.
